cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CC 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to predict unseen but plausible concepts conveyed by noun-noun compounds. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves training compositional models on observed compounds, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of negative evidence to capture generalizations over data suggests the involvement of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves querying the model for plausibility, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of distributed representations suggests the involvement of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
